  "prompt": "How did Oliver Sykes damaged his voice exactly?",
  "response": "Oliver Sykes, the lead vocalist of the British rock band Bring Me the Horizon, has experienced vocal issues over the years primarily due to the strenuous nature of his aggressive vocal techniques and extended touring schedules. Screaming and growling, which are common in the metal and hardcore genres, can be particularly taxing on vocal cords if not done with proper technique and care.\n\nIn 2019, Sykes revealed that he had ruptured a vocal cord during the band's tour, which forced them to cancel certain performances. Vocal cord ruptures are serious injuries that can arise from excessive vocal strain, poor technique, fatigue, or lack of proper vocal care.\n\nTo recover and prevent further damage, Sykes likely received medical treatment, vocal therapy, and possibly adjusted his vocal techniques and routines. The incident serves as a reminder of the importance of proper voice care, especially for vocalists in demanding genres.",
